# Google Health API v4 – Comprehensive Summary

## Overview

- **API Name:** Google Health API (v4)
- **Base URL:** `https://health.googleapis.com/`
- **Description:** View and manage health and fitness metrics and measurement data.
- **Documentation:** [developers.google.com/health](https://developers.google.com/health)
- **Protocol:** REST, Discovery v1

## Authentication & Scopes

The API uses OAuth 2.0. The following scopes are defined:

| Scope | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `cloud-platform` | See, edit, configure, and delete Google Cloud data |
| `googlehealth.activity_and_fitness.readonly` | See activity and fitness data |
| `googlehealth.ecg.readonly` | See ECG data |
| `googlehealth.health_metrics_and_measurements.readonly` | See health metrics and measurements |
| `googlehealth.irn.readonly` | See Irregular Rhythm Notifications data |
| `googlehealth.location.readonly` | See exercise GPS location data |
| `googlehealth.profile.readonly` | See profile data |
| `googlehealth.settings.readonly` | See settings |
| `googlehealth.sleep.readonly` | See sleep data |

> **Note:** Most methods require `cloud-platform` for subscriber/subscription management. User data methods use the specific readonly scopes.

## Resources & Methods

### 1. `projects.subscribers` (Cloud Project Subscribers)

Manage webhook endpoints that receive notifications.

| Method | HTTP | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `create` | POST | Register a new subscriber endpoint. **Requires endpoint verification** (see below). |
| `list` | GET | List all subscribers in the project. |
| `patch` | PATCH | Update subscriber config (endpoint URI, configs, authorization). Re-verifies if endpoint_uri or endpoint_authorization changed. |
| `delete` | DELETE | Delete a subscriber (optionally force delete child subscriptions). |

#### Endpoint Verification Process (Critical)

> **Verification with Authorization:**  
> POST to `endpoint_uri` with header `Authorization: <secret>` and body `{"type": "verification"}`. Expect HTTP `201 Created`.  
> **Verification without Authorization:**  
> POST to `endpoint_uri` without `Authorization` header, body `{"type": "verification"}`. Expect HTTP `401 Unauthorized` or `403 Forbidden`.  
> Both tests must pass for creation/update to succeed.

### 2. `projects.subscribers.subscriptions` (User Subscriptions)

Link a user to a subscriber for specific data types.

| Method | HTTP | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `create` | POST | Create a subscription for a user (requires `MANUAL` policy). |
| `list` | GET | List subscriptions, filterable by `user` and `data_type`. |
| `patch` | PATCH | Update data types for an existing subscription. |
| `delete` | DELETE | Delete a subscription, stopping notifications. |

**Subscription Create Policy:**
- `AUTOMATIC`: No need to create subscriptions; notifications sent based on user consents.
- `MANUAL`: Must call `CreateSubscription` for each user.

### 3. `users` (User Data)

| Method | HTTP | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `getProfile` | GET | Get user profile (age, stride lengths, membership start). |
| `updateProfile` | PATCH | Update profile (e.g., stride lengths). |
| `getSettings` | GET | Get user settings (units, timezone, language). |
| `updateSettings` | PATCH | Update settings (e.g., glucose unit, height unit). |
| `getIdentity` | GET | Get legacy Fitbit user ID and Google Health user ID. |
| `getIrnProfile` | GET | Get Irregular Rhythm Notification profile (onboarding, enrollment). |

### 4. `users.dataTypes.dataPoints` (Health Data Points)

Core CRUD and aggregation operations.

| Method | HTTP | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `get` | GET | Get a single identifiable data point. |
| `list` | GET | Query data points with filters (time range, civil time, etc.). |
| `create` | POST | Create a single data point. |
| `patch` | PATCH | Update an existing data point. |
| `batchDelete` | POST | Delete up to 10,000 data points. |
| `reconcile` | GET | Reconcile data from multiple sources into one stream. |
| `rollUp` | POST | Roll up data over physical time intervals (max 90 days, 14 for some types). |
| `dailyRollUp` | POST | Roll up data over civil time intervals (daily windows). |
| `exportExerciseTcx` | GET | Export exercise in TCX format (requires `?alt=media` for HTTP clients). |

#### Filter Syntax (for `list` and `reconcile`)

Supports filtering by time fields. Examples:

```
steps.interval.start_time >= "2023-11-24T00:00:00Z" AND steps.interval.start_time < "2023-11-25T00:00:00Z"
weight.sample_time.physical_time >= "2024-08-14T12:34:56Z"
sleep.interval.end_time >= "2023-11-24T00:00:00Z" AND sleep.interval.end_time < "2023-11-25T00:00:00Z"
```

Supported fields: `interval.start_time`, `interval.civil_start_time`, `sample_time.physical_time`, `sample_time.civil_time`, `date` (daily summaries), `interval.civil_start_time` (sessions), `electrocardiogram.interval.start_time`, `sleep.interval.end_t

